    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-01-03T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-01-03T09:00:00-05:00" n="541"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d541">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320/1–352: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting Chairman of the United States Delegation to the
                        General Assembly</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Roosevelt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-01-03T15:00:00+01:00"
                            >January 3, 1952—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 829. For Hickerson and Warren<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d541fn1">George L. Warren, Adviser on Refugees and Displaced
                        Persons.</note> from Sandifer. I want to emphasize in strongest terms
                    political necessity for approving <gloss target="#t_USGADel1">USGADel</gloss>’s
                    request for authorization to abstain on Goedhart’s proposal for assistance fund
                        (<gloss target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 828<note n="2" xml:id="d541fn2"
                        >Dated January 3, <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note>). Specific and
                    limited character of Goedhart’s proposal as presented Comite Three makes
                    abstention <pb facs="0860" n="838" xml:id="pg_838"/> possible without
                    stultifying our basic position. In peculiar political atmosphere this <gloss
                        target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_USGADel1">USGADel</gloss>
                    cannot afford loss of good will and prestige involved in voting in very small
                    minority perhaps of one against limited and popular Goedhart proposal.
                    [Sandifer.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
